SUMMARY:The Future Of Food Robotics - Northwest Robotics Alliance
DESCRIPTION:​Lee Kindell\, CEO of Moto Pizza\, has a vision of a fully autonomous restaurant where customers walk up\, pay at a kiosk\, and receive a beautifully crafted\, high-quality pizza in 10 minutes\, made by robotics and delivered via drone. \n​Join NWRA as we explore how soon this fully autonomous restaurant will become reality\, where this vision has stumbled along the way\, and what’s next in food robotics and automation technology. \n​Feel free to share this invite with your network! \nMeet the Panelists\n– ​Lee Kindell\, CEO of Moto Pizza\n​ – Clayton Wood\, Food Industry Venture Partner (Redstick Ventures)\, Chief Strategy Officer (CIBOTICA)\, and former CEO of Picnic\n​ – Parker Owan\, Ph.D\, Founder & CEO of Velodex Robotics\, previously Cruise and Amazon Robotics \n​Agenda\n​ – 5:30pm Networking begins\, light refreshments available\n– 6:00 Announcements & panel discussion\n– 7:00 Networking resumes\n– 8:00pm Event concludes
URL:https://www.geekwire.com/calendar-event/the-future-of-food-robotics-northwest-robotics-alliance/
LOCATION:Fresh Consulting\, 14725 SE 36th St Suite 300\, Bellevue\, WA\, 98006\, United States
CATEGORIES:Meetups
