SUMMARY:ctrl+alt+create live: Vibe Coding for Everybody
DESCRIPTION:https://ctrlaltcreate.live/ \nAnybody Can Build Software with AI. No Experience? We’ll Help You Get Started. \nOne Registered Participant Will Get a $100 Amazon Gift Card! \nPresented by Every\, this is a community-oriented\, beginner-friendly workshop series that’s fun for techies & non-technical people alike. \nRegister to participate either in-person (in Seattle) or online. \nIf you need to use AI but don’t know where to start\, this is for you. If you’ve been building with AI\, then you’re also welcome! \nWe’ll help you build something in just 2 hours. Fast\, fun\, and zero skills required. And if you know what you’re doing\, great! \nFor an idea of what can be done\, check out these 160+ apps! \nSeriously\, Anyone Can Build Something. \nWe’re bringing together non-technical users with big ideas and technical users who share a passion for AI and vibe coding. It’s a creative melting pot where curiosity meets capability. \nLearn how to begin: We show you how to use AI tools that respond to plain English. It’s easy to get started with vibe coding. \n2-Hour Sprint: Fast\, high-energy\, and satisfying. You could walk away with a real project or prototype. \nLow Stakes\, High Reward: Experiment without fear. Plus\, a random attendee will get a $100 Amazon Gift Card! \nIn-Person & Virtual: We host regular workshops in tech hubs like Seattle\, while welcoming virtual participants from anywhere in the world. \nAll Ages Welcome: Kids and students are encouraged to participate alongside adults. \nWho Is This For? \nThe Daydreamer: Would-be entrepreneurs who have never launched their own idea. Turn “what if” into a functional prototype in two hours. \nThe Idea Hunter: Curious entrepreneurs waiting for inspiration to strike. Test concepts quickly and find your next big venture. \nThe Tech-Adjacent: People who work in tech but aren’t software developers. Master the tools that allow you to build without engineering tickets. \nThe Upskiller: Looking for work or better positioning? Build a portfolio of AI-powered projects to prove your value in the modern workforce. \nThe Creative: Artists\, designers\, or writers. Learn how to bridge the gap between your imagination and a working digital product. \nThe Experimenter: This is your chance to try AI tools or build with low stakes. No pressure\, no wrong answers—just create. \nThe Simple 4-Step Process: \nShow up with a computer (join in-person or online). \nWe crowdsource ideas for a creative word to build around. \nTell your favorite AI what you want it to make. Then… iterate! We help you along the way. \nWe demo some work and give away the $100 Amazon Gift Card after the survey! \nRegister for FREE Seattle spots are limited — grab yours before they’re gone! \nWhat’s This Event Like? \nFun! And family friendly – bring your kid(s) if they have an imagination! Watch the most recent in-person event. \nAlso Welcoming: \nStartup Thinkers: You want feedback\, collaborators\, or potential connections. This is the perfect place to test ideas and meet co-conspirators. \nBored Developers: Tired of Jira tickets? Miss building for fun? Experiment with modern tools in a space full of people who love the joy of creating.We are grateful to be able to use this venue. \nAnd\, yes\, we are always looking for sponsors! \nFor your convenience\, we’ll add you to a list to be notified of all future events. Some sponsors may be contacting attendees after the event for follow-up. \nStay Connected: \nDiscord: https://discord.gg/XRBTM8sAMX \nEmail Updates: https://ctrlaltcreatelive.substack.com/ \nContact chris@pirillo.com for help. \nPlease register even if you can’t make it in-person to participate\, as you can still qualify for the $100 Amazon gift card giveaway!
URL:https://www.geekwire.com/calendar-event/ctrlaltcreate-live-vibe-coding-for-everybody-2/
LOCATION:Foundations\, 1605 Boylston Ave\, Seattle\, 98122\, United States
CATEGORIES:Artificial Intelligence
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/png:https://cdn.geekwire.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/CACL-Logo-1.png
END:VEVENT
