SUMMARY:Certificate in Modern AI Methods Information Session
DESCRIPTION:The graduate certificate in Modern Artificial Methods is a new program offered by the Paul G. Allen School of Computer Science & Engineering at the University of Washington. The work-compatible\, one-year program is designed to support recent graduates and industry professionals in using\, implementing\, and understanding in-depth artificial intelligence and machine learning tools and applying them in the workplace. The certificate is designed for those with STEM or business backgrounds\, with courses in prominent areas of AI\, including computer vision and natural language processing. Classes meet in-person on the University of Washington campus in Seattle. \nModern AI Methods program highlights:\n– Build knowledge and skills in core and emerging areas AI and ML for a rapidly-evolving workplace\n– Become more than a consumer of these technologies: understand how they work\, their advantages\, and their limitations\n– Connect with a cohort of local professionals in STEM while developing marketable skills\n– Learn from world-class instructors at one of the nation’s top computer science programs\n– Earn just your certificate\, or count it toward a UW master’s degree in AI and ML for Engineering\, or Multidisciplinary Engineering \nJoin the Allen School for an upcoming online information session to learn more!
URL:https://www.geekwire.com/calendar-event/certificate-in-modern-ai-methods-information-session/
LOCATION:Zoom
CATEGORIES:Artificial Intelligence,Educational events
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://cdn.geekwire.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/steve-johnson-_0iV9LmPDn0-unsplash-2.jpg
ORGANIZER;CN="Paul G. Allen School of Computer Science &amp%3B Engineering":MAILTO:kbeck@cs.washington.edu
END:VEVENT
